config.prompt:
Read every piece of legible text, signage, and license plates that appears anywhere across this security camera video. Text may only be readable for a moment (e.g. someone briefly holds up an ID or badge), so scan all frames, not just the first.

Respond with ONLY a JSON object - no prose, no code fence - with exactly two keys:
  "text":     the full extracted text as a single string, multiple items separated by a pipe "|" character (e.g. "FEDEX|7BCV928"). Lowercase the text so downstream matching is case-insensitive. Use "none" when no text is legible.
  "has_text": boolean, true when at least one piece of text was read, false otherwise.

Do not invent characters. If you can't clearly read a character, leave it out. Skip generic stuff like brand watermarks on the camera UI itself.

Examples:
  {"text": "fedex|7bcv928", "has_text": true}
  {"text": "ups|conway construction", "has_text": true}
  {"text": "none", "has_text": false}
